        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} We discovered the Ofterwang Horn from the mountain at noon and found it interesting. So it should just go there today. Our hiking app showed us several cable cars up the mountain. Among other things, the Ossi Reichert-Bahn. Since I had already seen signs on the street, I just decided there. The journey was not very long but nice up the mountain through small towns. When we arrived, we unfortunately had to find that there is no up here in summer. Well, there are other cable cars that go up to the horn. Someone will be on, because running up the mountain is too steep again and we were too lazy. No sooner said than done. On the other side of the mountain, the mountain railway World Cup Express is also open in summer. So back into the car, around the mountain and off the mountain with the cable car. </p>
        <p> At the top we hiked around the horn on a well -developed hiking trail over a cow pasture. We first enjoyed the view over the Gunzesrieder valley in which many pastures and smaller forests were seen and everything seemed very natural. Also definitely a nice place for hikes in a wild nature. </p>
        <p> On the second half of the circular hiking trail we got a great view of the valley between Sonthofen and Oberstdorf. Only over the mountains, in the distance there are a few decolors that will take good care of our many photos. </p>
