        <p> Since the hiking trail was not very long, we decided to run down the mountain without a break. First it went along the mountain range to a luxury hotel. From there it went through beautiful forests, which were overgrown with ferns in places, along wildflowers and hay meadows. </p>
        <p> Once at the bottom, we decided to go drinking in an economy and make a plan for the rest of the afternoon. Since the surrounding cable cars always close so early, we decided to simply take the car to the S&ouml;llereck to the new cable car. There to walk up the train again and then run the rather steep way back to the car. The descent was really steep but always fun and always well -asphalted, so that you could also enjoy the view while running. </p>
        <p> Tomorrow it will go to Bad Hindelang and the valleys Dahiter. There we want to explore the area to the Vilsalpsee. </p>
